================================================================================
Optional / link-time dependencies (not shipped as source here)
================================================================================

Depending on build options and your environment, this project may link against
or require separately installed third-party libraries. You must comply with the
license terms of any such library that you distribute or use with your product.

  Hesai ROS driver (hesai_ros_driver) — typical build-time / link-time deps:

  * yaml-cpp - MIT; used for YAML configuration (https://github.com/jbeder/yaml-cpp)
  * Boost C++ Libraries - Boost Software License 1.0; at least Boost.Thread
    (https://www.boost.org/LICENSE_1_0.txt)
  * CMake Threads / POSIX Threads - see your platform libc/pthread licensing

  Bundled Hesai SDK (submodule) and optional features:

  * OpenSSL - https://www.openssl.org/source/license.html (when TLS/mTLS PTC
    is enabled; default build may link this via WITH_PTCS_USE)
  * CUDA toolkit - see NVIDIA documentation when GPU UDP parser is enabled
  * PCL, LASlib - see respective project licenses (optional targets under SDK
    tool/, e.g. visualization / conversion tools)

  PCAP replay in this tree reads .pcap files with in-source parsers and does
  not link libpcap; only add libpcap (or similar) if you combine this software
  with external capture stacks that require it.

  When built as a ROS 1 or ROS 2 package, the ROS middleware, build tools
  (catkin / ament), and message/runtime packages (e.g. roscpp, rclcpp,
  sensor_msgs) are separate works; follow your ROS distribution and each
  package's license terms.

Nothing in this section changes the Modified BSD terms above for Hesai's own
code in this repository.

